  <li><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/010627.html"><b>&quot;Thorough
    File Check&quot; Violation of Personal Rights?</b></a><br>
    <font color="#072876"><i>[Quote from original post: The program is more than
    likely doing a full CRC of every file in the EQ directory, and checking it
    with a server version of the CRC. The complexity of the check is likely the
    cause, and it could also be your computers speed]</i></font><br>
    <br>
    Indeed. Pressing the button issues a full CRC check of every file on the
    required files list for EverQuest and downloads a new version if the local
    and remote CRCs differ. We found that a few people were suffering some file
    corruption that wasnt being noticed by our normal method of version control,
    so implemented this method for those cases.<br>
    <br>
