  <li><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/010570.html"><b>Thoughts
    on the 3D Engine</b></a><br>
    <font color="#072876"><i>[Quote from original post: Since the graphics
    engine should be entirely abstract from any gameplay and networking (for the
    most part) issues why cant the engine simply be upgraded and the old engine
    still be available for those who use lesser hardware]</i></font><br>
    <br>
    Its not so much &quot;cant&quot; as it is &quot;cant feasibly be done with
    reasonable time and resources&quot;. The art used in EverQuest represents
    nearly 4 years of work for a team of artists. Going through and revamping
    all of EQ proper with updated textures would take roughly half that time for
    a full team. Now, if you are talking about a completely new engine, it would
    then take additional man-years of work by programmers.<br>
    <br>
    New zone geometry, though not being possible for a platform that has to be
    backward compatible for people using the current engine, would have to match
    up in every way at every coordinate, so there wouldnt be much of a benefit
    there either.<br>
    <br>
    Basically, its not feasible because by the time wed get EQ rebuilt in the
    suggested fashion, all of the next-generation games would be out, and wed
    have an old game with a fresh look. Wed rather, when that time comes, have a
    new game with a fresh look.<br>
    <br>
    <br>
  <li><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/010564.html"><b>Necros
    and Lifetaps</b></a><br>
    The resistability or lack thereof of any spell is subject to the immunity of
    the target. In other words, even the &quot;nearly unresistable&quot; lifetap
    isnt going to work against a creature that is immune to magic.<br>
    <br>
    <br>
  <li><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/010537.html"><b>VI
    = Very Irresponsible?</b></a><br>
    <font color="#072876"><i>[Quote from original post: My compnay let us off
    early on Friday for the long weekend, so I went home and played some
    Everquest before dinner ]</i></font><br>
    <br>
    My company let us off early for the weekend as well :) I believe that the
    only patch that went up was a new patch program to enable some more verbose
    file checking.<br>
    <br>
    Previously, wed heard of some people experience some file corruption
    problems that arent caught by the standard version-control procedure. This
    patch gives an option for a more thorough check (a full CRC check) on the
    installed files. In other words it should not longer be necessary for tech
    support to recommend a full re-install to people who are reporting strange
    problems.<br>
    <br>
    The patch shouldnt at all affect gameplay, so theres really no issue with
    the timing for when it was put up. Im sorry you are upset, but did this
    patch reduce your ability to play the game at all?<br>
    <br>
    <br>
