  <li><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/010135.html"><b>Patches</b></a><br>
    <font color="#072876"><i>[Quote from original post: I find the constant
    posting of patches in either PDT, EST, PST ? its all lost on me. I’m sure
    a lot of us out there would appreciate this.]</i></font><br>
    <br>
    Were GMT-8, meaning that its 8 hours later in Greenwich. As far as posting
    it, we want to try and confuse the smallest number of people possible. For
    part of the world, we dont even get the date right as it is :)<br>
    <br>
    <font color="#072876"><i>[Quote from original post: its unfair to a HUGE
    amount of players who potentially after upwards of a years play will just be
    approaching the level required to encounter Gods]</i></font><br>
    <br>
    I understand your feelings on this. Frankly, could it be avoided we would.
    From an RP perspective, across many fantasy worlds created in novels and
    such, the power of a deity is based upon the number or strength of their
    followers. Thats basically whats happening in Norrath, a combination of
    both.<br>
    <br>
    From a loot perspective, we will indeed be moving thier current loot down to
    creatures powered similarly to what the deities are now. The deities will be
    populated with level 60 loot and become an appropriate encounter for a large
    group in that level range. Indeed, this will raise the bar for encountering
    a deity, however killing deities is supposed to be the pinnacle of success
    in EverQuest. So is encountering dragons, however in that case we decided to
    place the level cap on the old dragons to keep them within reach.<br>
    <br>
    <br>
