  <li><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/010130.html"><b>Getting
    Gloves to Proc</b></a><br>
    <font color="#072876"><i>[Quote from original post: If the combat system
    does indeed go to an equipment slot to see if your gloves are magical
    whenever you punch could the programmers add a few lines of code there so
    that whenever the combat system checks for magic status it could also do a
    test to see if the gloves proc an effect?]</i></font><br>
    <br>
    These are very different situations, and Im sorry but I cant explain it much
    more detail. In the case you mentioned, the hand, foot, shoulder slots are
    not accessed upon each hit. The ability of a character to hit, kick, slam
    magic creatures is set for the character upon equipping or removing the
    item, rather than by accessing the item upon each combat round. Sometimes
    the way something appears to work isnt the way it works from a mechanics
    standpoint. Its sort of like us being unable to make potions stackable. The
    fact that alcohol is stackable and activatable is completely separate from
    the idea of making potions that are stackable and activatable.<br>
    <br>
    <br>
  <li><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/010068.html"><b>Unannounced
    Change in Mountain Giants?</b></a><br>
    <font color="#072876"><i>[Quote from original post: Well i have been camping
    mountin giants for a few weeks now, solo with my jboots, im a 34 wizard and
    it seemed at first they had a very LOW resistance to Bonds of Force and
    Root, well since the last patch they are resisting those spells almost every
    other cast and i am getting trampled, I would just like to know if i was
    getting extremely unlucky or it was an unnanounced change, thank you]</i></font><br>
    <br>
    To be honest, I really dont know if the changes mentioned above occurred,
    but its not really something thatd Id go check on either. We dont announce
    standard tweaks to NPCs, as that is part of gameplay that is subject to
    change at any time. I will tell you that NPC resistances versus a particular
    line of spells cannot be set separately, so if they are more resistant its
    probably because their magic resistance was increased.<br>
    <br>
    <br>
